                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="alert alert-success" id="recent-changes">
                <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">📝 Recent Changes (v1.00 - Jan 9, 2026)</h3>
                <ul style="margin: 5px 0 0 20px;">
                    <li><strong>Initial Documentation:</strong> Created comprehensive documentation for AiConversation model</li>
                    <li><strong>Message Threading:</strong> Documented conversation-to-message relationships</li>
                    <li><strong>Helper Methods:</strong> Documented display_title, message_count, and latest_message helpers</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <section id="overview">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    The <strong>AiConversation</strong> model (Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/AiConversation.pm) 
                    provides a database schema for managing AI chat sessions in the Comserv application. It is a DBIx::Class Result class that supports:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>User-specific conversation creation and management</li>
                    <li>Conversation threading with message history</li>
                    <li>Conversation status tracking (active, archived)</li>
                    <li>Flexible metadata storage for conversation context</li>
                    <li>Automatic timestamp management (created_at, updated_at)</li>
                    <li>Helper methods for conversation display and analysis</li>
                    <li>Cascade deletion of messages when conversation is deleted</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    AiConversation serves as the foundation for the AI Chat System (E.1 integration), 
                    allowing users to maintain separate conversation threads with AI assistants and access 
                    complete chat history with metadata context.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="schema">
                <h2>Database Schema & Fields</h2>
                
                <h3>Table: ai_conversations</h3>
                <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Store AI conversation sessions, user associations, and conversation metadata</p>
                <p><strong>Primary Key:</strong> id (auto-increment)</p>
                <p><strong>Indexes:</strong> user_id (for fast user conversation lookup)</p>
                
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Field Name</th>
                        <th>Data Type</th>
                        <th>Nullable</th>
                        <th>Default</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>auto_increment</td>
                        <td>Primary key - auto-generated conversation ID</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>user_id</td>
                        <td>INTEGER</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>REQUIRED</td>
                        <td>Foreign key to User table - identifies conversation owner (REQUIRED)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>title</td>
                        <td>VARCHAR(255)</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>Human-readable conversation title/subject (optional, "New Conversation" if NULL)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>created_at</td>
                        <td>TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>Timestamp when conversation was created (auto-set)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>updated_at</td>
                        <td>TIMESTAMP</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE</td>
                        <td>Timestamp when conversation was last modified (auto-updated)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td>status</td>
                        <td>ENUM('active', 'archived')</td>
                        <td>NO</td>
                        <td>'active'</td>
                        <td>Conversation status: 'active' (ongoing) or 'archived' (closed/historical)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>metadata</td>
                        <td>LONGTEXT</td>
                        <td>YES</td>
                        <td>NULL</td>
                        <td>JSON or text metadata storage (context, settings, custom fields, etc.)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </section>

            <section id="relationships">
                <h2>Relationships & Message Threading</h2>
                
                <h3>Many-to-One Relationships</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>belongs_to 'user':</strong> The user who owns this conversation
                        <ul>
                            <li>Foreign Key: AiConversation.user_id → User.id</li>
                            <li>Usage: <code>my $user = $conversation->user;</code></li>
                            <li>Cascade: NO (user deletion doesn't automatically delete conversations)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>One-to-Many Relationships</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>has_many 'ai_messages':</strong> Messages in this conversation thread
                        <ul>
                            <li>Foreign Key: AiMessage.conversation_id → AiConversation.id</li>
                            <li>Cascade Delete: YES (deleting conversation deletes all associated messages)</li>
                            <li>Usage: <code>my @messages = $conversation->ai_messages->all;</code></li>
                            <li>Purpose: Provides chronological message history for the conversation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Message Threading Structure</h3>
                <p>Conversations are containers for related AI messages:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Conversation:</strong> One conversation per user-initiated chat session</li>
                    <li><strong>Messages:</strong> Individual messages within the conversation (user + AI)</li>
                    <li><strong>Chronology:</strong> Messages ordered by created_at timestamp</li>
                    <li><strong>Context:</strong> Conversation metadata provides additional context</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="conversation-lifecycle">
                <h2>Conversation Lifecycle & Status Management</h2>
                
                <h3>Conversation Status Values</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>'active'</strong> - Conversation is ongoing and can receive new messages (default on creation)</li>
                    <li><strong>'archived'</strong> - Conversation is closed/historical and should not receive new messages</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Typical Conversation Lifecycle</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Creation:</strong> User initiates new conversation → status = 'active'</li>
                    <li><strong>Active Phase:</strong> Messages exchanged between user and AI assistants</li>
                    <li><strong>Updated Tracking:</strong> updated_at timestamp refreshed with each new message</li>
                    <li><strong>Archival:</strong> User closes conversation → status = 'archived'</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical Access:</strong> Archived conversations accessible for reference/audit</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Metadata Field Usage</h3>
                <p>The metadata field supports flexible JSON storage for conversation context:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>AI Agent Type:</strong> Which agent handled the conversation (MainAgent, ReviewAgent, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Model Configuration:</strong> Which AI model was used (Claude, GPT-4, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Context Tags:</strong> Topic classification (support, documentation, code-review, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Custom Settings:</strong> Conversation-specific parameters (temperature, model, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Integration Data:</strong> References to external systems or data sources</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="api-methods">
                <h2>API Methods & Helpers</h2>
                
                <h3>Standard DBIx::Class Methods</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Creating Conversations:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $conversation = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->create({
    user_id => 42,
    title => 'Database Schema Migration Discussion',
    status => 'active',
    metadata => '{"agent_type": "MainAgent", "model": "Claude"}',
});</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Retrieving Conversations:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $conv = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->find(5);
my @active = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->search({
    user_id => 42,
    status => 'active'
})->all;
my @recent = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->search({
    user_id => 42
}, { 
    order_by => { -desc => 'updated_at' },
    rows => 10
})->all;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Updating Conversations:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>$conversation->update({
    status => 'archived',
    title => 'Updated Title'
});

$conversation->title('New Title');
$conversation->status('archived');
$conversation->update;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Helper Methods</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>get_display_title():</strong> Get conversation title or default</p>
                    <pre><code>my $title = $conversation->get_display_title();
# Returns: $conversation->title if set, else 'New Conversation'</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>get_message_count():</strong> Count messages in conversation</p>
                    <pre><code>my $count = $conversation->get_message_count();
# Returns: Number of AiMessage rows with this conversation_id</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>get_latest_message():</strong> Retrieve most recent message</p>
                    <pre><code>my $last_msg = $conversation->get_latest_message();
if ($last_msg) {
    print "Last message: " . $last_msg->content;
    print "From: " . $last_msg->role;
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Relationship Queries</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Access Messages:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my @messages = $conversation->ai_messages->all;
my @sorted = $conversation->ai_messages->search(
    {},
    { order_by => { -asc => 'created_at' } }
)->all;
my $msg_count = $conversation->ai_messages->count;</code></pre>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p><strong>Access Owner:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>my $owner = $conversation->user;
my $owner_name = $conversation->user->username;</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="examples">
                <h2>Usage Examples</h2>
                
                <h3>Example 1: Create New Conversation for User</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $user = $schema->resultset('User')->find(42);
my $conversation = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->create({
    user_id => $user->id,
    title => 'Kubernetes Migration Discussion',
    status => 'active',
    metadata => JSON::MaybeXS::encode_json({
        agent_type => 'MainAgent',
        model => 'Claude',
        context_tags => ['infrastructure', 'k8s', 'deployment']
    })
});

print "Created conversation #" . $conversation->id . "\n";</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 2: Retrieve User's Active Conversations</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $user = $schema->resultset('User')->find(42);
my @active = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->search({
    user_id => $user->id,
    status => 'active'
}, {
    order_by => { -desc => 'updated_at' }
})->all;

foreach my $conv (@active) {
    my $title = $conv->get_display_title();
    my $msg_count = $conv->get_message_count();
    print "- $title ($msg_count messages)\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 3: Display Conversation History</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $conversation = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->find(5);

print "Conversation: " . $conversation->get_display_title() . "\n";
print "Status: " . $conversation->status . "\n";
print "Created: " . $conversation->created_at . "\n";
print "Messages: " . $conversation->get_message_count() . "\n\n";

my @messages = $conversation->ai_messages->search(
    {},
    { order_by => { -asc => 'created_at' } }
)->all;

foreach my $msg (@messages) {
    print "[" . $msg->role . "] " . $msg->content . "\n";
    print "  (" . $msg->created_at . ")\n\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 4: Archive Completed Conversation</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $conversation = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->find(5);

if ($conversation->status eq 'active') {
    $conversation->update({ status => 'archived' });
    print "Conversation archived\n";
} else {
    print "Conversation already archived\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 5: Update Conversation Metadata</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>use JSON::MaybeXS;

my $conversation = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->find(5);
my $meta = decode_json($conversation->metadata || '{}');

$meta->{tags} = ['resolved', 'archived'];
$meta->{resolution_time} = time();

$conversation->update({
    metadata => encode_json($meta)
});

print "Metadata updated\n";</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Example 6: List Recent Conversations with Preview</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre><code>my $user = $schema->resultset('User')->find(42);
my @recent = $schema->resultset('AiConversation')->search({
    user_id => $user->id
}, {
    order_by => { -desc => 'updated_at' },
    rows => 5
})->all;

foreach my $conv (@recent) {
    my $title = $conv->get_display_title();
    my $msg_count = $conv->get_message_count();
    my $last_msg = $conv->get_latest_message();
    my $preview = substr($last_msg->content, 0, 50) if $last_msg;
    
    print "[$conv->id] $title\n";
    print "  Messages: $msg_count | Status: " . $conv->status . "\n";
    print "  Last: $preview...\n";
    print "  Updated: " . $conv->updated_at . "\n\n";
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="troubleshooting">
                <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
                
                <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Conversation Has No Title</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Conversation.title is NULL, causing display issues</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> Always use get_display_title() helper:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Helper returns "New Conversation" if title is NULL</li>
                            <li>OR: Set title when creating conversation: <code>title => 'Initial Topic'</code></li>
                            <li>OR: Use auto-generated title from first message content</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Messages Not Appearing</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> get_message_count() returns 0 even though messages were added</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> Check message-conversation association:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Verify messages have correct conversation_id set</li>
                            <li>Check message creation: <code>conversation_id => $conv->id</code></li>
                            <li>Verify relationship is properly loaded: <code>$conversation->ai_messages()</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Invalid Status Value</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Database error when setting status to invalid value</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> Status is ENUM with only 2 valid values:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Valid: 'active' or 'archived' ONLY</li>
                            <li>Invalid: 'pending', 'completed', 'draft', etc.</li>
                            <li>Use: <code>$conv->status('archived');</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Metadata Storage Issues</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Metadata not saved or causes charset errors</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> Metadata field is flexible but requires proper encoding:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Store as JSON: <code>encode_json($hash)</code></li>
                            <li>Retrieve as JSON: <code>decode_json($conversation->metadata)</code></li>
                            <li>Field is LONGTEXT: supports up to 4GB of data</li>
                            <li>NULL is allowed if no metadata needed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Cascade Delete Not Working</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Deleting conversation leaves orphaned messages in ai_messages table</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cascade delete IS configured and should work automatically:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Verify database cascade constraints are properly set</li>
                            <li>Manually delete messages if cascade doesn't work: <code>$conversation->ai_messages->delete;</code></li>
                            <li>Then delete conversation: <code>$conversation->delete;</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Timestamps Not Auto-Updating</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> updated_at not changing when conversation is modified</p>
                    <p style="margin: 5px 0;"><strong>Solution:</strong> MySQL triggers handle auto-update:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Ensure database has AUTO UPDATE trigger on ai_conversations table</li>
                            <li>Verify MySQL version supports CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE</li>
                            <li>Fallback: Manually set: <code>updated_at => DateTime->now</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

